    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>130600</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>67.1483</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>28</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ς</orig>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name> 
                            <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_νος" type="patronymic"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">νου</seg></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="4"/><placeName type="ethnic">Θεσ<supplied reason="lost">σαλό</supplied>ς</placeName>
                    <lb n="5"/><rs type="office" key="hegemonepandron"><w lemma="ἡγεμών"><supplied reason="lost">ἡ</supplied>γεμὼν</w> <w lemma="ἐπί">ἐπ᾿</w><w lemma="ἀνήρ">ἀ<supplied reason="lost">νδ</supplied>ρῶν</w></rs>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
                <app loc="5">
                    <lem resp="#rosamilia2023">ἐπ᾿ἀ<supplied reason="lost">νδ</supplied>ρῶν</lem>
                    <rdg resp="#IGCyr">ἐπ᾿ἀρῶν</rdg>
                </app>
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>fils de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos, thessalien, commandant de garnison.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>son of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos, Thessalian, commander of garrison.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>figlio di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>nos, tessalo, capo di presidio.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This inscription has no parallel and raises different questions. As noticed in the first edition, the use of the koine is a clue for an international context, perhaps in relation 
               with the Ptolemaic domination. The layout confirms that <foreign xml:lang="grc">Θεσσαλός</foreign> is here used with its original value of an ethnic 
               and not as a personal name. The latter would have stood at line 3. It is not clear whether line 2 was inscribed or left blank.</p>
              <p>Dobias-Lalou's reading of line 5 in the first edition was duly eliminated by Rosamilia who was able to identify the title <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἡγεμὼν ἐπ᾿ἀνδρῶν</foreign>, mainly attested at Cyprus, often associated with 
                  <foreign xml:lang="grc">φρούραρχος</foreign> and used for majors commanding a garrison (see <bibl><ptr target="#bagnall1976"/>, pp. <citedRange>51-54</citedRange></bibl>. As shown by Rosamilia, this is the first clear clue for the presence of a Lagid garrison at Cyrene after 250. 
              However, in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr097400</ref> some military Lagid officers of low rank are also attested.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
